  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then take a knob of<strong> butter</strong> out of the fridge and set aside to soften</p><p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and discard, then chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>sweet potato[es] </strong>(skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1671538045128-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1671538045128-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1671538045128-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1671538045128-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1671538045128-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped aubergine</strong> and <strong>sweet potato</strong> to the pan with the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the onion has softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1671538056281-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1671538056281-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1671538056281-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1671538056281-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1671538056281-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine a pinch of your <strong>berbere seasoning </strong>with the <strong>softened butter</strong> in a bowl and mix it all together, then set aside – this is your <strong>berbere-spiced butter</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>red lentils</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>remaining berbere seasoning </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pot with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and give everything a good mix up and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
