        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>egg[s]</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat (salt prevents the egg from cracking)</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 8 min for a perfect, mid-boiled egg, then fill a bowl of very cold water and add the<strong> soft-boiled egg[s]</strong> to the bowl until cooled</p><p>Set aside, then once cooled, peel the <strong>cooled soft-boiled egg[s] </strong>and cut them in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
